f=Product/ux/custom/research-repository/SKILL.md · in=reuse-first memory everything company learned about users: findings tagged product, persona, journey stage, linked PRDs decisions they informed. new study starts querying cheapest study one already done. · p=Teams re-run interviews because nobody remembered last round's answer. queryable repository turns research disposable event compounding asset, makes "we already know this" checkable claim. · wu=BEFORE any new study (study-design's mandatory first step query before you run)., PRD opportunity-assessment needs evidence (spec cites repo IDs)., New findings land (synthesis-discipline files them here) voice-of-customer verbatims arrive. · st:/ Protocol=QUERY-FIRST (every research request first searches repo: known? partially? stale?) verdict: ANSWERED (cite existing finding, new study) STALE (re-validate, don't re-discover) GAP (new study justified hands study-design) FILE (findings tagged: product `<FILL_IN profile>`, persona, journey stage, confidence, date; linked PRD/decision IDs used them) LINK (bidirectional: finding knows which decisions cite it; PRD knows evidence) AGE (findings carry date; old findings about changed product flagged stale, trusted silently). · in=Query before you run study request repo search bounced; "we already know this" answered, assumed (the reuse-first gate, ux's cheapest-study rule). Tag retrieval: finding nobody find finding doesn't exist product/persona/journey tags mandatory, optional metadata. Confidence rides finding (synthesis-discipline's flag): claim interviews claim 400-response survey cited way. Findings age: date-stamped, flagged stale product/market they describe moved staleness declared, never silently trusted (metric's version-break, research edition). Bidirectional links: repo records which PRDs/experiments used finding, disproven finding trace downstream decisions (annealing input shipped miss trace stale finding). · of=Repo entry: finding tags (product/persona/journey) confidence date source study cited-by (PRD/experiment IDs). Query result: ANSWERED/STALE/GAP refs. · pr=Query first cheapest study one already run., Tagged invisible; confidence-flagged uncitable., Findings age say so. · f=Empty repo (new company)? first studies seed it; query-first still runs (returns GAP honestly) discipline place finding #1. · b:with Other Skills=study-design consumes GAP verdicts (only real gaps get new studies); synthesis-discipline files findings confidence; voice-of-customer-intake feeds continuously., spec cites repo IDs PRDs (the evidence supply); shipped miss routes back check stale-finding cause (anneal)., Behavioral Science (future): persuasion/bias frameworks dept's tags dependency, doesn't inline pop psychology.